parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Deteriorated Insulation on Engine Wiring Harness
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The deteriorated insulation on the engine wiring harness can cause electrical shorts, leading to engine stalling, loss of power, and potentially, fires. This can result in accidents, injuries, or fatalities.

The premature deterioration of the insulation on the wires can cause short circuits, leading to sudden acceleration, stalling, and engine surging, which can result in accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
The failure of the throttle actuator wiring harness can cause sudden acceleration, which can result in accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
The failure of the cooling system link can cause coolant leaks, engine damage, and electrical system malfunctions, which can result in accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
